{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0168JoAdQA469Sx1rFandf3e","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpackage utils\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"fmt\"\n5\t\t\"strings\"\n6\t\n7\t\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/sets\"\n8\t)\n9\t\n10\tconst (\n11\t\tControllerNameKey = \"controller\"\n12\t\tOperandLabelKey   = \"multiarch.openshift.io/operand\"\n13\t\tOperatorName      = \"multiarch-tuning-operator\"\n14\t)\n15\t\n16\tconst (\n17\t\tArchitectureAmd64   = \"amd64\"\n18\t\tArchitectureArm64   = \"arm64\"\n19\t\tArchitecturePpc64le = \"ppc64le\"\n20\t\tArchitectureS390x   = \"s390x\"\n21\t)\n22\t\n23\tconst (\n24\t\tArchLabel                  = \"kubernetes.io/arch\"\n25\t\tNodeAffinityLabel          = \"multiarch.openshift.io/node-affinity\"\n26\t\tPreferredNodeAffinityLabel = \"multiarch.openshift.io/preferred-node-affinity\"\n27\t\t// PreferredNodeAffinitySourcesAnnotation tracks the complete audit trail of which\n28\t\t// configurations (ClusterPodPlacementConfig or PodPlacementConfig) attempted to set\n29\t\t// preferred node affinity for which architectures on a pod.\n30\t\t//\n31\t\t// Format: Comma-separated list of entries, where each entry follows:\n32\t\t//   architecture:weight:source[:skipped]\n33\t\t//\n34\t\t// Fields:\n35\t\t//   - architecture: CPU architecture (amd64, arm64, ppc64le, s390x)\n36\t\t//   - weight: Integer weight from NodeAffinityScoring plugin configuration (1-100)\n37\t\t//   - source: Configuration source that attempted to set this preference\n38\t\t//             Either \"ClusterPodPlacementConfig\" or \"PodPlacementConfig-<name>\"\n39\t\t//   - skipped: Optional suffix indicating this architecture was skipped because\n40\t\t//              it was already set by a higher-priority configuration\n41\t\t//\n42\t\t// Example:\n43\t\t//   \"arm64:30:PodPlacementConfig-high-priority,amd64:50:ClusterPodPlacementConfig:skipped\"\n44\t\t//\n45\t\t// This annotation provides transparency for debugging preferred